cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with task-oriented dialogue systems and user simulators. It also involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of intelligent agents and their training. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of data-driven models for user simulation and the development of a new State2Seq model. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on software development, but rather on the development of a framework for training dialogue agents. 

cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on user experience or interface design, but rather on the development of a user simulator for training dialogue agents.
